-- Romania’s OMV Petrom Appoints Secosan as Executive Board Member
-- B y   A n d r a   T i m u
-- 2012-07-13T05:42:34Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-07-13/romania-s-omv-petrom-appoints-secosan-as-executive-board-member.html
OMV Petrom SA (SNP) , Romania’s biggest oil
company, said it appointed Cristian Secosan as a member of its
executive board, responsible for gas and power operations.  Secosan replaces Hilmar Kroat-Reder, who gave up his
mandate in the Romanian company and will remain a board member
at  OMV AG (OMV) ’s units in  Turkey , Petrom said in a statement sent to
the Bucharest Stock Exchange today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Andra Timu in Bucharest at 
 atimu@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
James M. Gomez at 
 jagomez@bloomberg.net  